Input:
    Raw document collection D = {d1, d2, ..., dn}
    Document metadata M = {m1, m2, ..., mn}
    Chunk size L
    Chunk overlap O
    Embedding model Emb(·)

Output:
    Rice-domain document knowledge base KB
    Vector index I

1. Initialize KB as an empty collection
2. Initialize Chunk_List as an empty list

3. For each document d_i in D do

4.     Load document d_i according to its file type
           Supported formats may include PDF, DOCX, TXT, HTML, CSV, and structured records

5.     Extract raw text T_i from d_i

6.     Clean T_i:
           Remove page headers, footers, page numbers, references not used for QA,
           duplicated paragraphs, invalid symbols, broken line breaks, and OCR noise

7.     Normalize T_i:
           Standardize punctuation, units, variety names, disease names,
           pest names, growth-stage terms, and agricultural terminology

8.     Attach metadata m_i:
           source type, document title, publication year, author or institution,
           document category, crop topic, and original file path

9.     Split T_i into initial paragraphs P_i = {p1, p2, ..., pk}

10.    Merge short paragraphs when their semantic meaning is incomplete

11.    Divide the normalized text into semantic chunks C_i = {c1, c2, ..., cm}
           Each chunk should be close to length L
           Adjacent chunks preserve overlap O
           Chunk boundaries should avoid breaking disease descriptions,
           cultivation procedures, variety attributes, or standard clauses

12.    For each chunk c_j in C_i do

13.        Generate a stable chunk identifier:
               cid = document_id + "#" + chunk_index

14.        Build chunk metadata:
               chunk_id, document_id, source type, title, topic,
               start position, end position, and update timestamp

15.        Generate embedding vector:
               v_j = Emb(c_j)

16.        Store the following record into KB:
               <cid, c_j, v_j, chunk_metadata>

17.        Append <cid, v_j> to Chunk_List

18.    End For

19. End For

20. Build vector index I using all embedding vectors in Chunk_List

21. Save KB and I to persistent storage

22. Return KB and I
